									  LED Lights					
 
 
 
 
 
 




LED Lights












 
The emergence of LEDs as a useful alternative to incandescent lighting can be credited to new manufacturing technologies along with a growing awareness of the advantages of LEDs.
 
LED lighting offers some key advantages when compared to the old-fashioned incandescent light bulb invented by Thomas Edison:

Reduced energy use
Reduced heat generation
Increased life expectancy

Light-emitting diodes supply a low-energy source of lighting. LED fixtures used for lighting, as opposed to those used to create a glowing effect on signs and equipment, include numerous LEDs that together create white light that illuminates an area effectively.  LED lights hold a number of advantages in comparison to compact fluorescent light bulbs, or CFLs, the coiled bulbs that have replaced many traditional incandescent light bulbs
 
The energy-saving capacity of LED lights means:

They’re better for the environment than traditional forms of lighting.
Keep energy bills lower.
LEDs last for a long time, typically far longer than fluorescent bulbs.
Furthermore, LEDs are durable, not breaking as easily as bulbs.

The ability of LEDs to direct light in a specific direction is one of their primary benefits, while CFLs emit light in all directions.  CFL bulbs often fall short of their expected lifespans, LED lights typically come with at least three-year warranties, according to the EPA.
 
Use our energy saving LED Tubes as a retrofit or new installation. LED lights can be easily installed just like conventional lighting. As an example LED T8’s fit existing sockets with just a slight wiring modification. LED Fluorescent Light Replacements offer Bright Light, Low Heat with the Cost Saving and many have a feature of No Ballast required.
 
A wide variety of LEDs including T-8 tubes and Edison base screw in bulbs are available. Contact our office for specific pricing.
 
